          img(src='../img/game-of-thrones.jpg' alt='A Game of Thrones: The Board Game in progress')
          .caption
              | Photo credit:&nbsp;
              a.text-link(href="https://boardgamegeek.com/image/1318951/game-thrones-board-game-second-edition") @hoarmurath, on BGG
          .tags
            .tag
              .icon
                img(src='../img/puzzle.svg' alt='complexity')
              | More Complex
            .tag
              .icon
                img(src='../img/people.svg' alt='player count')
              | 3-6 Players
            .tag
              .icon
                img(src='../img/time.svg' alt='play time')
              | Playtime: 120-240 Minutes
            .tag
              .icon
                img(src='../img/designer.svg' alt='designer')
              | Designed by Christian T. Petersen
          p
            | A Game of Thrones: The Board Game is a territory control game that does justice to the series, with players acting as one of the high Houses - Stark, Baratheon, Lanister, Martell, Greyjoy, or Tyrell. It may take as much time to play as Risk, but GoT has many more mechanics to strategize around.
            br
            br
            | Each turn, players commit their units to perform actions like marching to attack an area, defending an area, and consolidating power. Players choose these actions without knowing the decisions of their opponents, but then they reveal and resolve them in turn order.
            br
            br
            | Preparing to attack in GoT is straightforward, but each House can play combat cards with varying strengths and abilities that can turn the tide of battle. Battling is not everything however; choosing to consolidate power will allow you to increase your standings on influence tracks, which can improve your turn order and give you access to more potent actions.
            br
            br
            | This game has everything you would want in a successor to Risk, including the chance to pull off an epic nail-biting victory. The GoT theming makes this game really stand out, and it‚Äôs fun to play as the characters you know and love. However, these mechanics are still great even if you‚Äôre not a fan of the series.
            br
            br
            a.text-link(href="https://amzn.to/3xSdO7w" rel= "nofollow" target="_blank") Buy #{rec3}: The Board Game on Amazon
            br
